How to Run Locally
Clone this repository

bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/flask-calculator.git
cd flask-calculator
Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended)

bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`
Install dependencies

bash
pip install flask

Create index.html in the templates/ folder

html
<!-- templates/index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Flask Calculator</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Simple Calculator</h2>
    <form method="POST">
        <input type="text" name="display" placeholder="Enter expression" required>
        <input type="submit" value="Calculate">
    </form>
    {% if result != '' %}
        <h3>Result: {{ result }}</h3>
    {% endif %}
</body>
</html>
Run the app
bash
python app.py

Open in browser
Navigate to http://127.0.0.1:5000/

âš ï¸ Disclaimer
This app uses Python's eval() which can be dangerous if not properly secured. Do not use this in production or expose it to untrusted users. For a safer alternative, use a math expression parser like sympy or asteval.

